headline: How The Narrative Around Trimble (TRMB) Is Shifting With New Tech Tailwinds And Valuation Tweaks
summary: Why Trimble’s Fair Value Moved, Even If Only Slightly Analysts have nudged their fair value estimate for Trimble from US$98.50 to US$99.75 while also adjusting the discount rate from 8.61% to 8.66% and trimming the revenue growth assumption from 6.52% to 6.43%. These fine tuning moves reflect how recent Street research is balancing Trimble’s exposure to areas like data centers, automation, electronics, test and measurement, and semiconductors against the execution challenges and broader...
